headline: New home sales, Lululemon earnings, Feb. PCE: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton preview several of the biggest economic data and earnings updates to come next week. February's new home sales are due out on Tuesday, March 25. The companies expected to release their latest earnings results include KB Home (KBH), Oklo (OKLO), GameStop (GME), Dollar Tree (DLTR), and Lululemon (LULU). Lastly, February's Personal Consumption Expenditures (PCE) index — the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation gauge — is set to come out on Friday, March 28. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.
